1
00:00:00,840 --> 00:00:03,240
Why do you have this?

2
00:00:03,980 --> 00:00:06,280
That's exactly what
I came here to find out.

3
00:00:06,850 --> 00:00:11,080
I'd like to know
why I have this golden toad...

4
00:00:11,080 --> 00:00:12,320
with your family's crest on it.

5
00:00:13,920 --> 00:00:15,150
Listen.

6
00:00:16,290 --> 00:00:17,290
Have you...

7
00:00:17,820 --> 00:00:20,830
had it since birth?

8
00:00:21,260 --> 00:00:23,500
Or did someone give it to you?

9
00:00:23,760 --> 00:00:27,230
I think
it was something my grandfather had.

10
00:00:27,470 --> 00:00:28,470
Your grandfather?

11
00:00:29,300 --> 00:00:31,200
I was told my grandfather...

12
00:00:31,800 --> 00:00:33,670
died saving me in a fire.

13
00:00:34,810 --> 00:00:36,980
So when I was placed in an infant home,

14
00:00:37,740 --> 00:00:40,610
this toad and a golden spoon
were left with me.

15
00:00:41,210 --> 00:00:44,020
You were adopted?

16
00:00:44,450 --> 00:00:45,450
Yes.

17
00:00:46,080 --> 00:00:48,820
My parents adopted my brother and me...

18
00:00:49,390 --> 00:00:51,560
and raised us very well.

19
00:00:54,360 --> 00:00:55,830
I had no idea.

20
00:00:55,990 --> 00:00:59,300
Actually, when I saw this crest
at your house,

21
00:00:59,660 --> 00:01:02,100
I started to wonder about it.

22
00:01:02,670 --> 00:01:06,100
If, by some small chance,
I was connected to your family,

23
00:01:06,340 --> 00:01:07,970
that would be a very big deal.

24
00:01:08,210 --> 00:01:10,810
You mean, because of marrying Jang Mi?

25
00:01:11,110 --> 00:01:13,510
Yes. That's part of it.

26
00:01:13,550 --> 00:01:17,550
I don't think you're related
to my family by blood,

27
00:01:17,950 --> 00:01:19,280
so you don't need to worry about that.

28
00:01:20,890 --> 00:01:25,020
I gave the golden toads with this crest...

29
00:01:25,790 --> 00:01:27,960
to people beyond my family as well.

30
00:01:29,030 --> 00:01:33,000
They were also gifts
for important business partners...

31
00:01:33,230 --> 00:01:35,170
or people I wanted to show my respects to.

32
00:01:35,730 --> 00:01:37,340
That's a relief.

33
00:01:37,340 --> 00:01:38,870
I was worried that I'm related
to your family by blood.

34
00:01:39,640 --> 00:01:41,940
I'm relieved now. Thank you, Chairman.

35
00:01:42,470 --> 00:01:45,040
There's nothing to thank me for.

36
00:01:46,110 --> 00:01:48,810
By the way, you said your grandfather...

37
00:01:49,310 --> 00:01:51,450
died in that fire.

38
00:01:52,220 --> 00:01:53,450
By any chance,

39
00:01:54,550 --> 00:01:58,120
besides your current name,

40
00:01:59,190 --> 00:02:02,360
- do you know of any other name you had?
- Yes.

41
00:02:02,630 --> 00:02:05,700
I'm told my birth name was Choi Ha Joon.

42
00:02:07,830 --> 00:02:11,240
You're Choi Ha Joon?

43
00:02:11,500 --> 00:02:12,500
Choi Ha Joon?

44
00:02:13,170 --> 00:02:14,470
Who's that?

45
00:02:14,970 --> 00:02:16,740
Judging by your surprise at my name,

46
00:02:17,010 --> 00:02:18,810
you must know something about me,
don't you?

47
00:02:19,610 --> 00:02:22,250
Whatever it is, please tell me everything.

48
00:02:26,180 --> 00:02:29,790
To think I'd get to see you like this...

49
00:02:30,790 --> 00:02:31,990
It's unbelievable.

50
00:02:33,020 --> 00:02:36,460
If you know my name,
then you must know about this toad too.

51
00:02:36,730 --> 00:02:39,600
Please tell me.
How did I end up with this?

52
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:44,600
I was going to ask you the same question.
Do you know how you got it?

53
00:02:44,770 --> 00:02:46,570
I heard from the director
of the infant home...

54
00:02:47,070 --> 00:02:49,910
that my nanny left it with me
when she brought me there.

55
00:02:50,640 --> 00:02:51,640
A nanny?

56
00:02:53,210 --> 00:02:54,250
Well...

57
00:02:55,110 --> 00:02:57,020
I see.

58
00:02:57,680 --> 00:03:00,850
There's something else
I want to ask you, sir.

59
00:03:01,490 --> 00:03:03,720
I learned the land
my late grandfather owned...

60
00:03:03,720 --> 00:03:06,520
is now the site of the Dream Hotel.

61
00:03:11,700 --> 00:03:12,700
You...

62
00:03:13,330 --> 00:03:15,000
You really are...

63
00:03:15,700 --> 00:03:19,500
Choi Myung Chul's grandson, Choi Ha Joon.

64
00:03:20,370 --> 00:03:22,940
You knew my grandfather?

65
00:03:22,940 --> 00:03:25,210
Of course I did.

66
00:03:25,440 --> 00:03:27,580
He and I were the best of friends.

67
00:03:28,150 --> 00:03:32,950
I'm the one who gave you this golden toad
and golden spoon as a first-birthday gift.

68
00:03:34,450 --> 00:03:37,120
So you and my grandfather
were best friends.

69
00:03:37,290 --> 00:03:40,560
Of course. How could I ever forget?

70
00:03:41,330 --> 00:03:43,930
If it hadn't been for that fire,

71
00:03:44,260 --> 00:03:48,900
I was planning to make your grandfather
an advisor at our Dream Hotel.

72
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:52,370
Then, do you happen to know...

73
00:03:52,370 --> 00:03:54,470
what caused the fire
at my grandfather's house?

74
00:03:55,170 --> 00:03:56,710
Something about it feels off to me.

75
00:03:58,640 --> 00:04:01,480
Feels off? In what way?

76
00:04:02,550 --> 00:04:06,150
What are they mumbling about?
I can barely hear them.

77
00:04:06,780 --> 00:04:10,390
Wait, does that mean
Lawyer Kang was adopted?

78
00:04:10,690 --> 00:04:12,660
He's a complete nobody.

79
00:04:21,130 --> 00:04:22,570
- Yes?
- Well...

80
00:04:24,170 --> 00:04:26,640
I apologize, sir. I didn't know
you were with Lawyer Kang.

81
00:04:26,640 --> 00:04:27,840
Right.

82
00:04:28,410 --> 00:04:31,280
Let's talk about your grandfather
some other time.

83
00:04:31,440 --> 00:04:35,210
- Something urgent just came up.
- Of course.

84
00:04:35,550 --> 00:04:38,080
You've answered my questions
about the golden toad.

85
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:40,050
Thank you for that,

86
00:04:40,350 --> 00:04:42,350
but I still have
so many more questions for you.

87
00:04:42,890 --> 00:04:45,390
Please, you have to tell me
what happened back then.

88
00:04:45,820 --> 00:04:48,560
- I'll be waiting.
- I will.

89
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:51,160
Anyway, it's good to see you.

90
00:04:51,430 --> 00:04:54,000
It's like my old friend
has come back from the dead.

91
00:04:55,470 --> 00:04:57,500
Funny how fate works, isn't it?

92
00:04:59,040 --> 00:05:00,940
- I'll see myself out.
- Okay.

93
00:05:05,040 --> 00:05:06,580
See you.

94
00:05:13,790 --> 00:05:15,950
Sir, did something happen?

95
00:05:24,930 --> 00:05:27,430
The Chairman and my grandfather
were best friends?

96
00:05:28,130 --> 00:05:29,830
Then why do I have such a bad feeling
about this?

97
00:05:30,670 --> 00:05:33,140
And why was he so shocked
when I said I was Choi Ha Joon?

98
00:05:39,510 --> 00:05:41,010
Choi Myung Chul...

99
00:05:41,510 --> 00:05:45,020
So you send your grandson to me like this.

100
00:05:45,780 --> 00:05:49,450
That's right, Myung Chul, my old friend.

101
00:05:50,350 --> 00:05:52,490
You haven't forgotten me after all.

102
00:05:53,560 --> 00:05:55,430
I understand completely.

103
00:05:56,260 --> 00:05:59,660
I have to get him and Jang Mi
married at once.

104
00:06:00,260 --> 00:06:03,900
- Sir, Lawyer Kang just...
- Yes.

105
00:06:04,500 --> 00:06:08,010
The sole survivor of that fire long ago,

106
00:06:08,410 --> 00:06:10,440
Choi Myung Chul's grandson, Choi Ha Joon,

107
00:06:11,180 --> 00:06:12,610
is none other than Lawyer Kang Baek Ho.

108
00:06:13,110 --> 00:06:14,780
Choi Ha Joon, you say?

109
00:06:16,150 --> 00:06:18,820
You mean Choi Ha Joon,
the top shareholder of Dream Hotel,

110
00:06:18,820 --> 00:06:20,990
who's only on paper?

111
00:06:24,620 --> 00:06:28,930
- How could Lawyer Kang Baek Ho be...
- The true owner of our hotel...

112
00:06:29,430 --> 00:06:31,600
is Lawyer Kang Baek Ho...

113
00:06:31,860 --> 00:06:33,870
who's about to marry our Jang Mi.

114
00:06:39,770 --> 00:06:41,310
How amusing.

115
00:06:42,240 --> 00:06:44,240
What an amusing world we live in.

116
00:06:44,910 --> 00:06:48,450
To think our fates
would be intertwined like this.

117
00:06:52,850 --> 00:06:54,920
According to
the former Chief of Staff's records,

118
00:06:55,350 --> 00:07:00,160
I heard the baby completely vanished,
and no one knew if he was dead or alive.

119
00:07:01,090 --> 00:07:03,960
So Choi Ha Joon is still
officially listed as a missing person.

120
00:07:05,030 --> 00:07:07,370
Secretary Kim, watch your mouth.

121
00:07:08,930 --> 00:07:10,740
Kang Baek Ho is not Choi Ha Joon.

122
00:07:10,740 --> 00:07:12,800
He's just someone
with the same name, got it?

123
00:07:13,500 --> 00:07:14,970
Yes, sir.

124
00:07:16,270 --> 00:07:19,540
If Chae Hwa Young gets wind of this,

125
00:07:20,680 --> 00:07:24,280
there's no telling what horrors
Kang Baek Ho will have to endure.

126
00:07:27,080 --> 00:07:30,990
Hong Ju,
you should have listened to me all along.

127
00:07:31,090 --> 00:07:33,590
How can you be such a poor judge
of character?

128
00:07:34,060 --> 00:07:38,830
Why do you always fall
for the empty suits?

129
00:07:38,900 --> 00:07:40,460
What are you talking about?
This is completely unexpected.

130
00:07:40,900 --> 00:07:42,700
- Who are you talking about?
- Who do you think?

131
00:07:42,700 --> 00:07:45,270
Lawyer Kang Baek Ho,
the one you're so crazy about.

132
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:47,440
What? What about Baek Ho?

133
00:07:47,640 --> 00:07:50,810
He's adopted, and he doesn't even know
who his biological parents are.

134
00:07:50,940 --> 00:07:53,080
Wait, Baek Ho was adopted?

135
00:07:53,380 --> 00:07:57,110
You wouldn't even look at the rich guy
I kept telling you about,

136
00:07:57,480 --> 00:07:59,720
and you only had eyes for Kang Baek Ho.

137
00:07:59,720 --> 00:08:01,150
See how that turned out?
It serves you right.

138
00:08:01,420 --> 00:08:05,260
So, Lawyer Han Young Ja adopted and raised
both Jun Ho and Baek Ho?

139
00:08:05,890 --> 00:08:06,960
That's incredible of her.

140
00:08:08,330 --> 00:08:10,290
But Mom, how do you know all this?

141
00:08:10,490 --> 00:08:13,330
I just heard it myself, loud and clear,
outside the study.

142
00:08:13,900 --> 00:08:15,970
Kang Baek Ho came to the Chairman...

143
00:08:15,970 --> 00:08:18,600
and said he's actually Choi Ha Joon.

144
00:08:19,100 --> 00:08:20,810
Then he was rambling on about something,

145
00:08:21,270 --> 00:08:24,280
and the Chairman totally freaked out,
asking him if he was adopted.

146
00:08:24,510 --> 00:08:28,610
- It was something like that.
- Wait, Mom, what did you just say?

147
00:08:28,850 --> 00:08:32,350
- You said Baek Ho is Choi Ha Joon?
- Yes, Choi Ha Joon.

148
00:08:32,820 --> 00:08:34,250
He said his real name is Choi Ha Joon.

149
00:08:34,650 --> 00:08:38,420
- So what?
- Seriously? Baek Ho is Choi Ha Joon?

150
00:08:40,290 --> 00:08:43,490
Hello? This is Ma Dae Chang.

151
00:08:43,630 --> 00:08:45,830
Hello, Chairman.

152
00:08:46,900 --> 00:08:48,100
What's this regarding?

153
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:51,540
I'm calling about the kids' wedding.

154
00:08:51,800 --> 00:08:54,040
I was hoping we could meet.

155
00:08:54,040 --> 00:08:56,340
Actually, I did hear about that.

156
00:08:56,910 --> 00:09:00,410
Jang Mi and Baek Ho
were thinking sometime next spring.

157
00:09:00,810 --> 00:09:03,710
They said with everything going on
in your family,

158
00:09:03,710 --> 00:09:06,520
they want to wait
until it's all resolved and settled.

159
00:09:06,680 --> 00:09:09,390
There's really no need for that.

160
00:09:10,620 --> 00:09:12,890
After what happened to Seo Rin,

161
00:09:13,520 --> 00:09:17,090
both Jang Mi and I have been
feeling so empty.

162
00:09:18,330 --> 00:09:23,170
But I can't tell you how reassuring it is
when Lawyer Kang visits here.

163
00:09:23,500 --> 00:09:27,410
So, I was hoping to have them get married
as soon as possible.

164
00:09:27,970 --> 00:09:30,580
I was wondering how things are
on your end.

165
00:09:32,510 --> 00:09:34,250
That works for us.

166
00:09:35,280 --> 00:09:38,450
Okay, then I'll talk it over
with Baek Ho...

167
00:09:38,520 --> 00:09:40,650
and get back to you.

168
00:09:40,850 --> 00:09:43,750
Yes, please. If you could hurry,
I'd appreciate it.

169
00:09:44,220 --> 00:09:46,220
I know it's a bit sudden,

170
00:09:47,020 --> 00:09:49,290
but I was hoping for the end of the month.

171
00:09:49,930 --> 00:09:51,030
Oh my goodness.

172
00:09:51,030 --> 00:09:53,630
To think your grandfather
and my grandfather were best friends.

173
00:09:53,830 --> 00:09:56,900
- We were connected all along.
- Tell me about it.

174
00:09:57,200 --> 00:10:00,740
I guess you and I are just meant to be.

175
00:10:00,910 --> 00:10:02,510
Of course we are.

176
00:10:03,410 --> 00:10:06,480
- What? Were you planning on leaving me?
- No.

177
00:10:07,140 --> 00:10:09,280
Relax. Can't you take a joke?

178
00:10:09,450 --> 00:10:12,720
I'm just worried
I might lose the one I love.

179
00:10:14,450 --> 00:10:17,760
I told the Chairman that I was adopted,

180
00:10:17,890 --> 00:10:19,560
but he didn't seem to mind at all.

181
00:10:20,120 --> 00:10:22,490
I was so worried
he'd have a problem with it.

182
00:10:22,830 --> 00:10:25,630
My aunt, the one we're looking for,
was in the same situation.

183
00:10:25,830 --> 00:10:29,170
So my grandfather
understands better than anyone.

184
00:10:29,770 --> 00:10:32,540
Looking at everything that's happened,
I guess it was fate after all.

185
00:10:32,640 --> 00:10:36,110
Our grandfathers had this amazing bond
before I was even born,

186
00:10:36,210 --> 00:10:39,480
and now you and I have found each other
and are getting married.

187
00:10:39,610 --> 00:10:42,350
"Getting married?"
That's bold talk coming from you.

188
00:10:42,910 --> 00:10:46,220
- Are you coming on to me now?
- Don't go overboard.

189
00:10:47,490 --> 00:10:50,050
Hey, why don't we get married first?

190
00:10:50,790 --> 00:10:52,620
Let's deal
with Chae Hwa Young first, though.

191
00:10:53,160 --> 00:10:56,760
By the way, you still have
Seo Rin's hospital receipt, right?

192
00:10:57,260 --> 00:11:00,430
That receipt completely shattered
Chae Hwa Young's alibi,

193
00:11:00,870 --> 00:11:02,970
but what else can we find out from it?

194
00:11:03,700 --> 00:11:05,840
We'll use it as bait.

195
00:11:06,570 --> 00:11:08,870
Let's make her make the first move.

196
00:11:09,340 --> 00:11:11,710
We wait for her to make a move,
and then we chase her down...

197
00:11:11,710 --> 00:11:12,780
and catch her.

198
00:11:14,450 --> 00:11:15,450
Let's go.

199
00:11:22,150 --> 00:11:23,890
Have you two completely lost your minds?

200
00:11:24,360 --> 00:11:26,990
Who do you think you are,
barging in here practically every day?

201
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:28,330
Get out! Now!

202
00:11:30,760 --> 00:11:33,260
That perfect alibi you were so proud of.

203
00:11:33,700 --> 00:11:36,130
Listen closely.
That's the sound of it all crumbling down.

204
00:11:36,370 --> 00:11:39,500
- What is this?
- License plate number 237BU8305.

205
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:41,710
That's your car, isn't it?

206
00:11:42,340 --> 00:11:44,040
Date of transaction, May 11.

207
00:11:44,540 --> 00:11:46,980
Time in, 8:53 a.m.

208
00:11:46,980 --> 00:11:49,310
Time out, 2:32 p.m.

209
00:11:49,750 --> 00:11:52,080
Location was Medical Public Parking
in Gyeonggi Ohjeong.

210
00:11:52,450 --> 00:11:54,850
May 11 was the very same day...

211
00:11:55,390 --> 00:11:58,660
Seo Rin died all alone
at Ohjeong Plastic Surgery.

212
00:11:59,090 --> 00:12:03,030
So how is it that the car of someone
who was supposedly at a massage parlor...

213
00:12:03,290 --> 00:12:05,130
was in the parking lot
of Ohjeong Plastic Surgery,

214
00:12:05,530 --> 00:12:08,300
and for nearly six hours at that?

215
00:12:08,530 --> 00:12:10,670
That's ridiculous.
Why would I have gone there?

216
00:12:11,270 --> 00:12:15,270
Manager Lee or Seo Rin
could have driven my car.

217
00:12:16,040 --> 00:12:20,280
Are you trying to frame me for murder
with a single scrap of a parking receipt?

218
00:12:20,480 --> 00:12:24,050
I expected you to play innocent.
That's the Chae Hwa Young I know.

219
00:12:24,580 --> 00:12:25,620
Just you wait.

220
00:12:26,150 --> 00:12:28,750
I'm going to expose
every single evil thing you did...

221
00:12:29,190 --> 00:12:32,460
in that hospital room
where my Seo Rin was suffocating to death.

222
00:12:33,120 --> 00:12:35,890
The fact that you were at that hospital,
at that time, on that day...

223
00:12:36,330 --> 00:12:37,530
will be proven without a doubt.

224
00:12:37,930 --> 00:12:39,430
Get out now!

225
00:12:39,960 --> 00:12:42,400
Who do you pieces of trash think you are,
threatening me?

226
00:12:42,800 --> 00:12:44,340
You think doing this
will bring Seo Rin back?

227
00:12:44,840 --> 00:12:46,970
Does taking your anger out on me
make you feel better?

228
00:12:47,040 --> 00:12:48,510
You might want to save your strength
for screaming later.

229
00:12:49,310 --> 00:12:52,980
You'll be doing a lot of talking
in an interrogation room very soon.

230
00:12:53,180 --> 00:12:54,680
You'd better stay up every night and wait.

231
00:12:55,410 --> 00:12:58,980
Because I'll be the first one there
with handcuffs just for you.

232
00:13:03,220 --> 00:13:04,260
What do you think you're doing?

233
00:13:04,920 --> 00:13:07,630
What do you think you're doing,
barging into the CEO's office so rudely?

234
00:13:07,630 --> 00:13:10,790
Ask your mother.
She knows exactly why we're doing this.

235
00:13:11,160 --> 00:13:13,460
And Jun Ho, don't cross the line again.

236
00:13:14,230 --> 00:13:17,970
I used to look up to you. So don't make me
put you in handcuffs myself.

237
00:13:18,040 --> 00:13:19,170
Get out.

238
00:13:19,170 --> 00:13:21,140
Get out of my sight right now!

239
00:13:23,840 --> 00:13:25,610
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

240
00:13:25,980 --> 00:13:27,140
This is my last warning to you.

241
00:13:27,750 --> 00:13:30,080
If you so much as lay a finger
on her again,

242
00:13:30,580 --> 00:13:31,980
I won't let it slide a second time.

243
00:13:31,980 --> 00:13:33,780
In other words, don't test my patience.

244
00:13:34,220 --> 00:13:35,220
Got it?

245
00:13:54,240 --> 00:13:57,410
Eat up while it's nice.
The broth is nice and rich.

246
00:14:01,510 --> 00:14:04,580
Oh my, it really is rich.
Honey, you have to try this.

247
00:14:04,920 --> 00:14:07,820
It's so light yet so rich.
This is the real deal.

248
00:14:10,050 --> 00:14:12,660
It turns out Jung Suk Hee
is her legally changed name.

249
00:14:13,320 --> 00:14:16,990
I'm currently confirming her real name
before she changed it.

250
00:14:17,730 --> 00:14:20,330
What about her time at the orphanage?

251
00:14:20,330 --> 00:14:22,430
Have you looked
into her friends back then?

252
00:14:22,770 --> 00:14:24,670
Ever since their time at the orphanage,
Oh Bok Gil...

253
00:14:25,040 --> 00:14:28,410
doted on Jung Suk Hee
like she was his own sister.

254
00:14:28,570 --> 00:14:29,940
So, then...

255
00:14:30,270 --> 00:14:33,540
you just need to check the records
from Oh Bok Gil's orphanage.

256
00:14:33,640 --> 00:14:38,050
I already did, but for some reason,
no records of Jung Suk Hee were left.

257
00:14:38,250 --> 00:14:39,450
Darn it.

258
00:14:40,990 --> 00:14:42,850
So what's our next move?

259
00:14:42,850 --> 00:14:44,190
Wait!

260
00:14:44,790 --> 00:14:49,330
That Park Young Mi
who pretended to be Eun Hye.

261
00:14:50,330 --> 00:14:52,660
She has to know something. Find her.

262
00:14:52,860 --> 00:14:55,370
I'm already on it. I'm tracking her.

263
00:14:56,800 --> 00:15:01,040
Right now, she seems to know the most
about the real Park Young Mi.

264
00:15:01,340 --> 00:15:03,140
Good. Find her quickly!

265
00:15:04,210 --> 00:15:08,150
I can't stand to watch Chae Hwa Young
run wild for another single day!

266
00:15:09,280 --> 00:15:12,080
Hurry and find my real Eun Hye.

267
00:15:22,130 --> 00:15:24,260
Yes. It could've just been
a random gesture,

268
00:15:25,300 --> 00:15:26,930
but for some reason,
after seeing her do that,

269
00:15:27,770 --> 00:15:30,000
she seemed to take after my sister,
Seong Sil.

270
00:15:34,310 --> 00:15:36,240
After hearing what she said,

271
00:15:36,240 --> 00:15:38,880
Jung Suk Hee
does look a bit like Seong Sil.

272
00:15:39,110 --> 00:15:41,010
Honey, hurry up and eat.

273
00:15:41,950 --> 00:15:43,280
It'll get soggy if you wait.

274
00:15:44,380 --> 00:15:46,280
Right, I'll eat.

275
00:15:47,550 --> 00:15:49,550
Hey, Suk Hee,
can I get a little more broth over here?

276
00:15:49,850 --> 00:15:51,960
Hey, don't just stand there staring.

277
00:15:53,220 --> 00:15:55,360
Alright. Eat up.

278
00:15:56,960 --> 00:15:58,100
Is she really...

279
00:15:59,500 --> 00:16:00,960
No, it can't be.

280
00:16:01,300 --> 00:16:02,970
The world may be small,

281
00:16:02,970 --> 00:16:06,170
but there's no way a girl like that
could be my daughter.

282
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:08,110
Absolutely not.

283
00:16:09,640 --> 00:16:11,210
Name, Choi Ha Joon.

284
00:16:11,210 --> 00:16:12,910
Born in 1993.

285
00:16:13,810 --> 00:16:16,850
He doesn't seem to be in the country.
Use any means necessary...

286
00:16:16,910 --> 00:16:18,580
and find him as fast as possible.

287
00:16:18,580 --> 00:16:21,020
Understood. I'll be in touch, sir.

288
00:16:21,350 --> 00:16:22,350
Okay.

289
00:16:26,460 --> 00:16:28,260
Jun Ho!

290
00:16:28,530 --> 00:16:29,830
What's all the fuss about?

291
00:16:29,890 --> 00:16:33,660
- You'll freak out too once you hear this.
- What are you talking about?

292
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:35,300
Have you found Choi Ha Joon?

293
00:16:36,600 --> 00:16:37,630
I think I did.

294
00:16:38,070 --> 00:16:39,070
Really?

295
00:16:39,770 --> 00:16:43,710
- You really found Choi Ha Joon?
- Well, I wouldn't say I found him...

296
00:16:45,480 --> 00:16:47,340
I'm not really sure myself.

297
00:16:47,610 --> 00:16:48,650
It's not confirmed, but...

298
00:16:48,650 --> 00:16:50,710
What is it? Stop beating around the bush
and just tell me.

299
00:16:51,550 --> 00:16:54,220
Where can I meet Choi Ha Joon?
Put me in touch with him.

300
00:16:54,280 --> 00:16:55,820
I need to meet him in person
and convince him.

301
00:16:56,350 --> 00:16:58,360
Convince him of what?

302
00:16:59,720 --> 00:17:02,330
Well, since he's
our company's largest shareholder,

303
00:17:02,990 --> 00:17:06,030
I wanted to discuss the future
of the hotel, things like that.

304
00:17:06,300 --> 00:17:07,400
That's it?

305
00:17:07,870 --> 00:17:09,230
Just tell me what you know already.

306
00:17:09,600 --> 00:17:12,100
Wait a minute.
Jun Ho is Chae Hwa Young's son.

307
00:17:13,170 --> 00:17:14,710
I almost made a huge mistake.

308
00:17:15,070 --> 00:17:17,070
If Chae Hwa Young finds out
Baek Ho is the largest shareholder,

309
00:17:17,140 --> 00:17:19,380
she might try to hurt him.

310
00:17:20,910 --> 00:17:21,910
It's nothing.

311
00:17:21,980 --> 00:17:24,450
What do you mean, it's nothing?
You clearly know something.

312
00:17:24,650 --> 00:17:25,750
So why won't you tell me?

313
00:17:26,420 --> 00:17:30,620
What could I possibly know?
I was just making a big deal over nothing.

314
00:17:31,260 --> 00:17:35,790
I'm just wondering why you were
so desperate to find Choi Ha Joon.

315
00:17:36,260 --> 00:17:37,960
So just go about your business.

316
00:17:38,130 --> 00:17:40,130
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

317
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:43,000
What's wrong with her?

318
00:17:55,410 --> 00:17:58,750
I hope Chae Hwa Young and Kang Jun Ho
don't try to pull anything else.

319
00:17:59,280 --> 00:18:00,280
Baek Ho.

320
00:18:00,880 --> 00:18:04,390
Seems like there are so many sides to you
I haven't seen.

321
00:18:06,120 --> 00:18:10,530
- My heart nearly stopped earlier.
- It did? Were you scared?

322
00:18:10,590 --> 00:18:12,660
"If you so much as lay a finger
on her again..."

323
00:18:14,530 --> 00:18:17,670
You were like the romantic lead
in a TV drama.

324
00:18:17,870 --> 00:18:20,940
So, Jang Mi, you like the alpha male type?

325
00:18:23,270 --> 00:18:26,710
You should have said so.
I can do that for you all day long.

326
00:18:27,740 --> 00:18:29,210
Oh, please.

327
00:18:32,920 --> 00:18:36,950
I can't wait to marry you.
I can't wait to have you all to myself.

328
00:18:38,060 --> 00:18:40,090
What if someone sees us? Let me go.

329
00:18:40,160 --> 00:18:43,190
Just one minute.
Let me just recharge like this.

330
00:18:45,200 --> 00:18:47,700
I thought you took the day off today.

331
00:18:47,870 --> 00:18:49,700
Why did you come in on your day off?

332
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:52,470
I could've taught Chae Hwa Young
a lesson all by myself.

333
00:18:53,740 --> 00:18:55,840
Absolutely not. Don't you know
what Chae Hwa Young is capable of?

334
00:18:56,010 --> 00:18:59,380
You never know what horrible thing
she's capable of.

335
00:18:59,440 --> 00:19:00,480
You know that.

336
00:19:02,380 --> 00:19:06,650
Promise me you'll never confront
Chae Hwa Young alone again.

337
00:19:07,120 --> 00:19:09,290
And that we'll handle things together,
no matter what.

338
00:19:09,590 --> 00:19:12,520
All right.
Then you have to promise me something too.

339
00:19:13,420 --> 00:19:15,560
That you won't do anything reckless
on your own.

340
00:19:21,370 --> 00:19:22,500
Jang Mi.

341
00:19:23,130 --> 00:19:24,600
I'll protect you until the very end.

342
00:19:36,050 --> 00:19:37,050
Baek Ho.

343
00:19:37,480 --> 00:19:39,880
The real owner of Dream Group was Baek Ho.

344
00:19:41,020 --> 00:19:42,620
I'm a great judge of character.

345
00:19:43,120 --> 00:19:44,990
That witch Oh Jang Mi,
how did she get so lucky?

346
00:19:45,820 --> 00:19:48,860
Darn it. She really hit the jackpot
late in life.

347
00:19:49,560 --> 00:19:52,200
She got a rich grandpa and Baek Ho,
the largest shareholder.

348
00:19:52,730 --> 00:19:56,370
Life is so unfair.
How can this be happening?

349
00:19:56,830 --> 00:19:59,570
Hong Ju, why are you just standing there?

350
00:19:59,570 --> 00:20:00,700
Do you want me
to get you something to drink?

351
00:20:02,170 --> 00:20:04,740
No. I won't drink anything from you.

352
00:20:05,340 --> 00:20:08,050
Though I'd happily drink anything
Baek Ho gives me.

353
00:20:13,580 --> 00:20:14,590
How ridiculous.

354
00:20:27,430 --> 00:20:30,100
Hong Ju, what's wrong?
Did something happen at work?

355
00:20:30,830 --> 00:20:33,370
Mom, I'm so upset I could just die.

356
00:20:33,870 --> 00:20:36,440
Why does Oh Jang Mi get
all the good things?

357
00:20:36,640 --> 00:20:38,340
What is it now?

358
00:20:38,410 --> 00:20:40,280
She went from a nobody working
at a side dish shop...

359
00:20:40,280 --> 00:20:42,650
to the Dream Group’s granddaughter.

360
00:20:43,010 --> 00:20:45,050
And Baek Ho,
the man she's head over heels for,

361
00:20:45,580 --> 00:20:47,420
is actually Choi Ha Joon,
the largest shareholder of Dream Hotel.

362
00:20:48,520 --> 00:20:49,650
So where does that leave me?

363
00:20:50,050 --> 00:20:51,490
What about me?

364
00:20:52,060 --> 00:20:53,360
Who did you say
is the largest shareholder?

365
00:20:53,420 --> 00:20:55,390
Who do you think it is?
It’s Lawyer Kang Baek Ho.

366
00:20:55,790 --> 00:20:57,160
Didn't you hear me?

367
00:20:57,930 --> 00:21:00,560
- I'm so upset.
- Oh my goodness. This is unbelievable.

368
00:21:01,470 --> 00:21:05,970
Kang Baek Ho is Choi Ha Joon,
and he's the largest shareholder?

369
00:21:06,270 --> 00:21:08,340
Yes! How many times do I have to tell you?

370
00:21:09,140 --> 00:21:13,880
Hong Ju, then, we need to make sure
we back the right horse.

371
00:21:15,110 --> 00:21:17,910
Are we just supposed to line up
behind whoever’s in power?

372
00:21:18,020 --> 00:21:19,820
Is our only job to fall in line?

373
00:21:19,880 --> 00:21:24,220
You silly girl. You're head over heels
for Kang Baek Ho.

374
00:21:24,660 --> 00:21:26,160
So you have to win him over, obviously.

375
00:21:26,960 --> 00:21:28,690
If you make Kang Baek Ho my son-in-law,

376
00:21:29,190 --> 00:21:33,330
- it's game over.
- Mom, get a grip.

377
00:21:33,600 --> 00:21:36,630
I keep throwing myself at him,
but he doesn't even bat an eye.

378
00:21:36,700 --> 00:21:38,400
He only has eyes for Oh Jang Mi.

379
00:21:38,670 --> 00:21:40,670
How am I supposed to
make him your son-in-law?

380
00:21:40,740 --> 00:21:44,070
Are you really my daughter?
Where's your ambition?

381
00:21:44,240 --> 00:21:47,110
Just because there's a goalie
doesn't mean you can't score.

382
00:21:47,680 --> 00:21:52,150
As they say, where there's a will,
there's a way.

383
00:21:52,320 --> 00:21:54,080
You've got to be kidding me.

384
00:21:54,720 --> 00:21:55,890
I need to think...

385
00:21:56,550 --> 00:22:00,660
about a plan to make Kang Baek Ho yours.

386
00:22:00,720 --> 00:22:04,730
Mom, if I could really be
in Baek Ho's arms,

387
00:22:05,030 --> 00:22:06,230
I'd have nothing more to wish for.

388
00:22:07,430 --> 00:22:11,100
You're saying Jang Mi made a deal...

389
00:22:11,400 --> 00:22:13,700
with the law firm
run by a lawyer named Tommy,

390
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:15,740
the secretary of Chairman Ali
who stayed at our hotel?

391
00:22:16,040 --> 00:22:17,440
It seems she colluded with Chairman Ali
beforehand...

392
00:22:17,710 --> 00:22:19,780
and used the escrow account
of Tommy's firm...

393
00:22:20,110 --> 00:22:22,280
to get the 30 million dollars
from CEO Chae.

394
00:22:22,510 --> 00:22:25,420
Right, she pulled that off
quite impressively.

395
00:22:25,820 --> 00:22:27,920
Jang Mi reported that to me.

396
00:22:28,150 --> 00:22:29,290
But, sir.

397
00:22:29,720 --> 00:22:32,120
That so-called Chairman Ali
was an impostor.

398
00:22:32,390 --> 00:22:33,390
An impostor?

399
00:22:33,390 --> 00:22:36,760
Chairman Ali in India published an article
that she was coming to Korea,

400
00:22:37,060 --> 00:22:39,260
but it was confirmed
that she never actually came.

401
00:22:39,530 --> 00:22:42,630
Then who was the Chairman Ali
staying at our hotel?

402
00:22:47,700 --> 00:22:49,670
This is the real Chairman Ali.

403
00:22:49,670 --> 00:22:50,740
And...

404
00:22:52,510 --> 00:22:53,910
this woman is the impostor.

405
00:22:57,250 --> 00:23:01,990
I can only see her eyes.
How am I supposed to know if she's fake?

406
00:23:02,190 --> 00:23:04,390
I had an expert
run a facial recognition analysis...

407
00:23:04,390 --> 00:23:06,020
on both photos.

408
00:23:06,290 --> 00:23:08,560
- They didn't match.
- Is that right?

409
00:23:08,960 --> 00:23:11,830
If Jang Mi was in on this with that woman,

410
00:23:13,100 --> 00:23:15,730
she's probably someone close to Jang Mi...

411
00:23:15,730 --> 00:23:17,830
or the person closest to Jang Mi.

412
00:23:19,070 --> 00:23:21,970
- Find out who she is.
- Yes, sir.

413
00:23:37,020 --> 00:23:38,020
No, wait.

414
00:23:39,690 --> 00:23:40,690
Is this...

415
00:23:44,490 --> 00:23:45,530
Jung Suk Hee?

416
00:23:49,170 --> 00:23:51,470
Mother, we're here for dinner.

417
00:23:51,570 --> 00:23:54,370
Welcome, Baek Ho. Make yourself at home.

418
00:23:54,500 --> 00:23:56,440
Mom, you didn't have to go
to all this trouble.

419
00:23:56,540 --> 00:24:00,840
Not at all. I made a ton of japchae,
Baek Ho's favorite,

420
00:24:00,980 --> 00:24:03,210
and was just about to ask you two over
for dinner anyway.

421
00:24:03,210 --> 00:24:04,580
I love japchae.

422
00:24:07,020 --> 00:24:08,520
Thank you for the meal.

423
00:24:11,320 --> 00:24:12,420
This is so delicious.

424
00:24:16,590 --> 00:24:20,100
How could someone like Jung Suk Hee...

425
00:24:21,000 --> 00:24:24,030
impersonate a giant
of international finance?

426
00:24:24,630 --> 00:24:25,670
That's...

427
00:24:28,610 --> 00:24:29,610
Has she...

428
00:24:30,870 --> 00:24:32,880
regained her senses?

429
00:24:33,410 --> 00:24:36,880
- Is that possible?
- If so, it would make sense.

430
00:24:37,780 --> 00:24:42,050
I heard she studied for the bar exam
and was quite brilliant back in the day.

431
00:24:42,220 --> 00:24:44,790
What about the background check
I asked for on Jung Suk Hee?

432
00:24:45,160 --> 00:24:48,190
Haven't you checked yet
if she's recovered or not?

433
00:24:48,490 --> 00:24:52,460
I've been busy confirming if Eun Hye
and Jung Suk Hee are the same person.

434
00:24:53,330 --> 00:24:56,330
Find out if Jung Suk Hee
is being treated at a hospital.

435
00:24:56,330 --> 00:24:57,900
And check on her condition.

436
00:24:58,030 --> 00:24:59,040
Yes, sir.

437
00:24:59,300 --> 00:25:02,110
And I found the address
of the fake Park Young Mi.

438
00:25:03,310 --> 00:25:05,410
I'm planning to have her identify
Jung Suk Hee tomorrow.

439
00:25:05,810 --> 00:25:09,610
Run a DNA test as well discreetly.

440
00:25:10,850 --> 00:25:13,220
Chae Hwa Young must not find out
under any circumstances.

441
00:25:13,420 --> 00:25:14,820
Yes, sir, I understand.

442
00:25:28,300 --> 00:25:29,300
Take a good look.

443
00:25:29,900 --> 00:25:32,470
Tell me if that woman
is the person you know.

444
00:25:37,510 --> 00:25:38,510
I'm not sure.

445
00:25:39,040 --> 00:25:40,880
It's been such a long time.

446
00:25:41,510 --> 00:25:43,880
Just seeing how much she's aged,

447
00:25:43,880 --> 00:25:45,020
I can't really tell at first glance...

448
00:26:00,160 --> 00:26:01,230
I think that's her.

449
00:26:07,440 --> 00:26:08,470
Seriously...

450
00:26:13,480 --> 00:26:14,480
Oh my goodness!

451
00:26:14,980 --> 00:26:18,210
Isn't that the fake one
who conned us before?

452
00:26:32,560 --> 00:26:34,200
That's right.

453
00:26:34,560 --> 00:26:39,140
The woman, Jung Suk Hee,
who left Suk Hee's Side Dishes earlier,

454
00:26:40,070 --> 00:26:44,070
is the real Park Young Mi
from the orphanage.

455
00:26:47,940 --> 00:26:49,650
This necklace.

456
00:26:50,850 --> 00:26:51,980
This necklace...

457
00:26:52,980 --> 00:26:56,620
you dared to present to me
as a token from Eun Hye last time.

458
00:26:57,020 --> 00:26:58,250
Take a good look.

459
00:27:00,120 --> 00:27:02,930
Yes. That's right.

460
00:27:02,930 --> 00:27:04,030
I just...

461
00:27:04,560 --> 00:27:07,960
bought an identical fake one.

462
00:27:08,030 --> 00:27:12,570
So you stole Eun Hye's name too?

463
00:27:12,640 --> 00:27:15,170
No, I didn't steal it.

464
00:27:15,710 --> 00:27:18,380
When Young Mi was adopted
by Mr. Jung's family,

465
00:27:18,640 --> 00:27:21,950
- I heard she changed her name.
- So...

466
00:27:23,450 --> 00:27:27,450
Do you know how Park Young Mi
became Jung Suk Hee?

467
00:27:27,680 --> 00:27:28,850
That?

468
00:27:28,850 --> 00:27:32,360
I already told CEO Chae everything
about it last time.

469
00:27:32,420 --> 00:27:33,420
What?

470
00:27:34,060 --> 00:27:36,830
You told CEO Chae everything?

471
00:27:36,990 --> 00:27:40,030
Yes. She was worried
another impostor might show up,

472
00:27:40,260 --> 00:27:42,600
so she said she needed to know everything.

473
00:27:43,300 --> 00:27:44,630
Chae Hwa Young.

474
00:27:45,300 --> 00:27:46,940
That she-devil.

475
00:27:47,240 --> 00:27:51,740
She knew all along my daughter Ma Eun Hye
is Jung Suk Hee.

476
00:27:56,150 --> 00:27:59,080
Tell me everything...

477
00:27:59,920 --> 00:28:01,420
you told CEO Chae.

478
00:28:02,090 --> 00:28:03,090
Now!

479
00:28:27,410 --> 00:28:28,950
(The First Man)

480
00:28:29,080 --> 00:28:31,150
Chae Hwa Young took the bait.

481
00:28:31,150 --> 00:28:33,520
Manager Lee is going to Ohjeong.

482
00:28:33,780 --> 00:28:35,950
We can catch him red-handed
trying to destroy the evidence.

483
00:28:36,520 --> 00:28:41,190
There was a small four-leaf clover
embroidered on my baby clothes.

484
00:28:41,590 --> 00:28:43,460
I'm the Chairman's daughter?

485
00:28:43,960 --> 00:28:47,230
So Jung Suk Hee is my Eun Hye.

486
00:28:48,060 --> 00:28:49,470
Father!

487
00:28:53,800 --> 00:28:55,810
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
